of%20executive%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeal%20Katyal%2C%20the%20former%20Acting%20Solicitor%20General%20and%20co-counsel%20of%20the%20Liberty%20Justice%20Center%2C%20which%20is%20representing%20VOS%20Selections%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20thinks%20Trump%20should%20listen%20to%20the%20ruling%20and%20study%20it%20instead%20of%20prolonging%20the%20matter%20by%20bringing%20it%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20he%20thinks%20these%20tariffs%20are%20so%20important%2C%20then%20he%20should%20go%20to%20Congress%20and%20get%20them%20approved%2C%26quot%3B%20Katyal%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVictor%20Schwartz%2C%20owner%20of%20VOS%20Selections%2C%20told%20BI%20following%20today's%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eruling%20that%20he%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ealready%20seeing%20layoffs%20and%20cutbacks%20due%20to%20the%20tariffs%2C%20and%20he%20hopes%20for%20a%20swift%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20going%20into%20our%20busiest%20time%20of%20the%20year%2C%20like%20many%20small%20businesses%20going%20into%20the%20holiday%20season%2C%20which%20means%20we're%20shipping%20the%20most%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Schwartz.%20That%20means%20we're%20going%20to%20be%20paying%20the%20most%2C%20so%20the%20biggest%20burden%20of%20the%20tariffs%20is%20just%20upcoming%2C%20and%20that%20means%20that%20burden's%20going%20to%20be%20passed%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20appeals%20court's%20decision%20is%20the%20second%20time%20the%20courts%20have%20ruled%20Trump%20overstepped%20his%20authority%3Cs%3E%20%3C%2Fs%3Ewhen%20he%20imposed%20sweeping%20tariffs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0starting%20with%20a%20baseline%2010%25%2C%20with%20some%20as%20high%20as%20104%25%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0on%20imports%20to%20the%20United%20States%20from%20almost%20every%20country%20around%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subsequent%20court%20battle%20has%20focused%20largely%20on%20the%20bounds%20of%20the%20president's%20executive%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolitical%20scientists%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcould-congress-stop-trump-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECongress%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E%20holds%20the%20constitutional%20authority%20to%20impose%20duties%20and%20levies%20upon%20other%20countries%2C%20except%20in%20carveouts%20created%20by%20the%20IEEPA%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20president%20to%20declare%20an%20emergency%20under%20the%20National%20Emergency%20Act%20to%20regulate%20or%20prohibit%20imports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupply%20chain%20experts%20and%20economists%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Trump's%20wide-reaching%20%26quot%3BLiberation%20Day%26quot%3B%20tariffs%20have%20affected%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-cost-consumers-thousands-food-clothes-price-increase-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eprices%20for%20everything%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20pantry%20staples%20like%20coffee%20and%20sugar%20to%20apparel%20and%20larger%20purchases%20like%20cars%20and%20appliances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20venues%20through%20which%20Trump%20could%20seek%20tariffs%20without%20Congress%2C%20including%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-may-happen-next-court-strikes-down-trumps-ieepa-tariffs-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESection%20232%20investigations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%20of%20which%20are%20already%20ongoing%20over%20resources%20like%20copper%20and%20timber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20White%20House%20spokesperson%20Kush%20Desai%20said%20that%20the%20tariffs%20remain%20in%20effect%20and%20that%20the%20administration%20looks%20forward%20to%20%26quot%3Bultimate%20victory%26quot%3B%20on%20this%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump%20lawfully%20exercised%20the%20tariff%20powers%20granted%20to%20him%20by%20Congress%20to%20defend%20our%20national%20and%20economic%20security%20from%20foreign%20threats%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Desai.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20ruling%2C%20Trump%20immediately%20responded%20on%20his%20social%20media%20platform%20that%20tariffs%20are%20%26quot%3Bthe%20best%20tool%26quot%3B%20to%20help%20workers%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmain-street-trump-trade-war-tariffs-small-businesses-impact-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esupport%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20added%20that%20the%20lawsuit%20will%20be%20taken%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappeals-court-strikes-down-donald-trump-sweeping-tariff-plan-scotus-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756505740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b2210ca17a8c5b4053cba0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappeals-court-strikes-down-donald-trump-sweeping-tariff-plan-scotus-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20federal%20appeals%20court%20found%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20tariff%20plan%20unconstitutional%2C%20ruling%20that%20he%20overstepped%20his%20executive%20power%20to%20write%20trade%20policy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktl%40businessinsider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert%2CKatherine%20Li)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A313%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappeals-court-strikes-down-donald-trump-sweeping-tariff-plan-scotus-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98No%20power%20to%20impose%E2%80%99%3A%20US%20court%20declares%20most%20tariffs%20illegal%3B%20Trump%20says%20'total%20disaster%20for%20country'%22%2C%22conte