%20larger%20necks%20and%20smaller%20heads%2C%20a%20martingale-style%20collar%20will%20be%20best%2C%20adds%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abwellnesscenter.com%2Fteam%2F-------amy-l.-pike%2C-dvm%2C-dacvb%2C-iaabc-cdbc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Amy%20L.%20Pike%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinary%20behaviorist%20and%20owner%20of%20Animal%20Behavior%20Wellness%20Center.%20This%20design%20keeps%20the%20collar%20from%20slipping%20over%20the%20dog's%20head%20when%20a%20leash%20is%20attached.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20best%20dog%20collar%20for%20any%20pup%20is%20one%20that%20fits%20well%20and%20is%20comfortable%20enough%20to%20leave%20on%20for%20long%20stretches%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20vets%20recommend%20collars%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ECollars%20are%20recommended%20whenever%20a%20dog%20is%20outside%20so%20someone%20can%20easily%20identify%20the%20dog%20and%20in%20case%20you%20need%20to%20grab%20hold%20of%20it%20to%20separate%20your%20dog%20from%20another%20dog%20safely.%20Collins%20says%20a%20collar%20also%20serves%20as%20a%20backup%20if%20your%20dog's%20harness%20gives%20way.%20If%20you're%20looking%20for%20gear%20to%20safely%20and%20comfortably%20walk%20your%20dog%2C%20we%20recommend%20outfitting%20your%20pup%20with%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-harness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20dog%20harnesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-no-pull-dog-harness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20no-pull%20dog%20harnesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20attaching%20their%20leash%20directly%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20safest%20collar%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ECollins%20says%20the%20safest%20collar%20should%20be%20adjustable%20to%20fit%20the%20dog's%20neck%20with%20room%20left%20over%2C%20be%20easy%20to%20remove%2C%20and%20carry%20a%20dog's%20identification%20tags%20securely.%20Also%2C%20consider%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20collar%3A%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20overburden%20a%20toy%20breed%20with%20hefty%20neckwear.%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20dog%20holds%20their%20head%20in%20a%20lower%20position%20with%20a%20collar%20on%20versus%20the%20collar%20off%2C%20then%20it's%20too%20heavy%2C%26quot%3B%20Pike%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey%20should%20be%20able%20to%20easily%20lift%2C%20lower%2C%20and%20turn%20their%20head%20with%20the%20collar%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20a%20martingale%20collar%20good%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMartingale%20collars%20are%20designed%20with%20an%20extra%20loop%20of%20fabric%20that%20tightens%20gently%20(but%20not%20too%20tightly)%20when%20pressure%20is%20applied.%20Hinsperger%20recommends%20them%20for%20most%20dogs.%20Martingale%20collars%20can%20be%20used%20for%20regular%2C%20everyday%20wear.%20When%20attached%20to%20a%20harness%20using%20a%20safety%20clip%2C%20martingale%20collars%20offer%20added%20security%20for%20dogs%20who%20tend%20to%20slip%20out%20of%20flat%20collars%20and%20harnesses.%20This%20is%20especially%20beneficial%20for%20breeds%20with%20long%20necks%20and%20small%20heads%2C%20such%20as%20greyhounds%20and%20Afghan%20hounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20a%20prong%20collar%20bad%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20recommended%20to%20avoid%20using%20prong%20collars%20and%20other%20aversive%20tools.%20Pike%20says%20that%20prong%20collars%20can%20cause%20serious%20injuries%2C%20such%20as%20puncture%20wounds%2C%20and%20may%20increase%20fear%20and%20anxiety%20in%20dogs%20by%20punishing%20them%20for%20pulling.%20This%20can%20damage%20the%20trust%20between%20a%20dog%20and%20their%20owner%20and%20may%20lead%20to%20behavioral%20problems%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EShould%20dogs%20wear%20collars%20at%20home%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EVeterinarians%20agree%20that%20it%20is%20best%20to%20take%20collars%20off%20whenever%20dogs%20play%20with%20one%20another%20or%20are%20at%20home%20alone.%20%26quot%3BFor%20ultimate%20safety%2C%20it's%20best%20never%20to%20have%20a%20collar%20on%20a%20dog%20at%20home%2C%20unless%20you%20are%20with%20them%20the%20whole%20time%2C''%20Collins%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20point%20is%20it%20can%20get%20caught%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20furniture%2C%20on%20another%20dog's%20collar%2C%20or%20a%20dog%20could%20get%20its%20teeth%20on%20the%20collar%2C%20or%20they%20could%20get%20their%20foot%20through%20it%20if%20it's%20too%20loose.''%20Since%20so%20many%20things%20can%20go%20wrong%2C%20removing%20the%20collar%20makes%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20tightly%20should%20a%20collar%20be%20worn%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20misconception%20is%20that%20two%20fingers%20should%20fit%20between%20the%20dog's%20neck%20and%20collar%20when%20it%20should%20really%20be%20looser.%20%26quot%3BIt%20should%20be%20loose%20enough%20so%20that%20it%20lies%20flat%20and%20the%20dog%20is%20not%20bothered%20by%20it%2C''%20Collins%20says.%20As%20for%20positioning%20on%20the%20neck%2C%20aim%20lower%20than%20the%20dog's%20larynx%2C%20closer%20to%20the%20shoulders.%20Collins%20says%20this%20avoids%20a%20sensitive%20area%20of%20the%20neck%20that%20can%20be%20damaged%20with%20too%20much%20pressure.%20Finally%2C%20the%20thickness%20of%20a%20collar%20relative%20to%20the%20size%20of%20the%20neck%20is%20important.%20He%20says%20thinner%20collars%20are%20for%20small%20neck%20circumferences%20only.%20All%20of%20the%20collars%20we%20tested%20were%20either%20%C2%BE-%20or%201-inch%20thick%2C%20which%20worked%20on%20our%20medium-sized%20dog%2C%20but%20most%20of%20them%20were%20available%20in%20%C2%BD-inch%20thickness%20in%20smaller%20sizes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-collars%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publishe